=head1 DESCRIPTION

The container of your media file. This information helps you understand
the overall structure and details of your media, including format,
duration, and track layout.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Duration => Num

The total duration of your media file, in seconds.


=head2 Format => Str

The format of your media file. For example: MP4, QuickTime (MOV),
Matroska (MKV), or WebM. Note that this will be blank if your media
file has a format that the MediaConvert Probe operation does not
recognize.


=head2 Tracks => ArrayRef[L<Paws::MediaConvert::Track>]

Details about each track (video, audio, or data) in the media file.



